latestPosts.caption:
Some of you may know that I have been hoping to get a raffia / wicker bag for a while… There are so many different choices available on the market but I finally decided to get this LP19 wannabe @louisvuitton 😛
.
The reason behind is mainly because of the bandeau and hair tie that I previously ordered from the #LVxTM collaboration 🍒 — thought they are a perfect match even I haven’t seen this bag in person… However, I didn’t realize this bag is so difficult to get in HK!! Have been waiting way before its launch on May 22 but then their system doesn’t allow customers to order it 🙈… Eventually, it’s my SA who works the magic out to transfer one from Beijing store so I can try it on before making any payment!! Thanks a lot and I really love this one so much!! I’m vacation-ready now but where (and when) should / can I go? 🤔😅
.
P.S. The #lvsidetrunk and #lvallinbb version are relatively so much easier to find in HK stores! No idea why HK stores always just selectively order part of the items from a particular collection 🙈
.

latestPosts.caption:
My previous post reminds me that I have completely forgotten to share this bag and the bandeau that I got from wave 2 🌸… I picked this bag simply because it’s more subtle and everything with cherry blossom on this bag are removable - the charm, and the pocket mirror!! Not that I don’t like the cherry blossom design of their bags! They are all very pretty in my opinion! And the cherry blossom with smiley face is really cute too 😍… But my main concern when getting a bag is the longevity in term of usage - I’m kind of worried whether I will keep on using the bag once the hype is gone… and that’s why I have chosen a plain colored bag from this wave that doesn’t shout “murakami” (also consistent with the reason why I picked a plain colored capucines from the 1st wave 😅)
.
P.S. But then I’m still debating whether I should order a speedy with 🍒 from the last wave! Haven’t pull the trigger yet because of the same concern above. What do you guys think? Should I get it or it’s enough as I already have a few bags from this collaboration? 🤔 But that bag takes 4 months to make before it can ship out 😣
.

latestPosts.caption:
For those who are @diorbeauty fans, you might know there’s currently a #summerdior event located @pacificplacehk from now until the end of this month! This #diorriviera event is my most anticipated event every year as their chosen venue were all very pretty in the previous few years (The GTA in Sai Kung in 2024, and the Fullerton Ocean Park Hotel in 2023)! However, this year they decided to move indoor to a shopping mall — have to say there’s no summer feeling at all.. and you can imagine there is also an unavoidable amount of strangers in the background of your pictures 🤦🏻‍♀️… Because of this, if you are planning to go have a look, pick a time as early as possible in the morning to avoid the crowd!
.
Note: You can skip the #diorcafe if food are not being offered to you for free (heard from my BA that they required booking deposit from the public time slot but the 4 tables for serving food - pic 4 - are located at the front row of a nearby restaurant instead of being located inside the pop-up area so it’s not very picturesque 😅)
.
P.S. This event has 3 special gifts which are the plate, the mitzah, and the scarf (pic 8, 9)… The eye mask (pic 11), on the other hand, is a purchasable item and it is exclusively available in the event at this moment!
.

latestPosts.caption:
The exhibition of <<Hermès in the making>> is finally in #shenzhenchina ! You can meet their craftsmen from different departments, learn how they make a watch, a piece of jewelry, the H gloves, their scarf, a Kelly bag, and understand how they repair a handbag in the exhibition! Apart from these “meet the expert” sessions, there are also a lot of things you can experience, including a try-on in their scarf-printing technique, as well as learning their saddle-stitching (if you have not been to #bagstagewithhermes workshop)… Among different stations, I would say their scarf making session is the most eye-opening for me! Didn’t realize there are so many steps involved in the making of one single scarf - apart from designing the pattern by individual artist, it also requires a specialist to separate the colors into different layers (frame 12), the making of “screens”, and the actual coloring step (frame 13) 😳 … Highly recommend everyone who loves @hermes to go as it is opened to public from now until June 1 (registration required; in case you need the info, you can leave a message below or message me directly 😉)!
.
P.S. I skipped “how to make a Kelly bag” and saddle stitching workshop in this exhibition but it still took me more than 3 hours to finish everything - because it took 1 hr for just the scarf-coloring demonstration 😅!!! So in case you are planning to go, please reserve more time (or even half a day) so you can enjoy everything in there ☺️
.

latestPosts.caption:
A quick stop in #guangzhou before heading back home… 
.
Passed by this place when we were on our way to the hotel for check-in and were attracted by the antique architectural complex 😍… After looking it up online, we found that it’s a recently opened park in #guangzhouchina 🇨🇳 
.
Situated on the shore of Haizhu Lake, this park was designed based on traditional Lingnan-style garden. The buildings themselves house different exhibition such as calligraphy, Chinese paintings, sculptures, porcelains, and Cantonese embroidery, etc… so tourists can get a glimpse of the flavor of Guangzhou! Outside in the gardens, there’re streams, bridges, cliffs, and ponds — which I preferred as the opportunities for photos are endless 📸… Overall, I’m glad we decided to visit this park! Love its relaxed setting… away from the craziness of the busy streets outside ☺️
.
📍广州市文化馆 - 广东省广州市海珠区龙潭立交与聚德路交叉口南200米

latestPosts.caption:
This is a bar 🍻??? I was puzzled when I stepped inside this place!! Yes, there’s music… there’re some customers… but no one is smoking and no one is talking loudly! In fact, the ambient is very relaxing!! There’s a courtyard outside, a viewing terrace, and a pool where you can swim (obviously I have chosen to row the boat 🤪)! It’s a perfect spot to unwind after a day of sightseeing ☺️
.
Note: As the name of this bar & restaurant suggested, this place was formerly a residence of the governor of Guangxi known as Yang Ziji. It was then transformed into bar & restaurant. There’s an ancient village nearby, known as Xingping Ancient Town, where you can get food / souvenirs / clothings! 
.
